# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — Frontend Standards

---

## File Structure

```
{{FRONTEND_APP_PATH}}/
├── app/                    # Routes / Pages
│   ├── (auth)/             # Auth-required layout group
│   └── (public)/           # Public layout group
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                 # Base UI components (from library)
│   ├── {{PROJECT_SLUG}}/  # Project-specific components
│   └── shared/             # Shared across features
├── hooks/                  # Custom React hooks
├── lib/                    # Utilities, API client, helpers
├── types/                  # TypeScript type definitions
└── styles/                 # Global styles, tokens
```

---

## Component Patterns

### Naming
- PascalCase for components: `LoadTable.tsx`, `CarrierForm.tsx`
- camelCase for hooks: `useLoads.ts`, `useCarrierForm.ts`
- kebab-case for routes/directories: `load-planner/`, `carrier-management/`

### Structure
- One component per file (colocate small helpers if tightly coupled)
- Export component as named export, not default
- Props interface defined in the same file, named `{Component}Props`

---

## State Management

- **Server state:** {{DATA_FETCHING_LIBRARY}} <!-- React Query / SWR / RTK Query -->
- **Client state:** {{CLIENT_STATE}} <!-- Context / Zustand / Redux -->
- **Form state:** {{FORM_LIBRARY}} <!-- React Hook Form / Formik -->
- **URL state:** Search params for filters, pagination, sorting

> Rule: Server state in the data-fetching layer. Client-only state in context/store. Never duplicate.

---

## Data Fetching

- All API calls go through a centralized API client (`lib/api.ts`)
- Always unwrap the response envelope: `response.data.data`
- Handle pagination from `response.data.pagination`
- Cache invalidation on mutations

<!-- IF {{FRONTEND_FRAMEWORK}} == "next" -->
### Next.js Specific
- Use Server Components for initial data fetch where possible
- Client Components for interactive elements
- `useRouter` for navigation, `useSearchParams` for query state
<!-- ENDIF -->

---

## Error Handling

- API errors caught in the API client layer, transformed to consistent shape
- Display user-friendly messages, log technical details
- Use error boundaries for unexpected crashes
- Toast notifications for action feedback (success/error)

---

## 4-State Rendering

Every data-driven component MUST handle all 4 states:

1. **Loading:** Skeleton UI matching the layout
2. **Error:** Error message + retry button
3. **Empty:** Illustration + message + CTA (if applicable)
4. **Data:** The actual populated UI

---

## Form Patterns

- Validation with Zod schemas (shared with backend when possible)
- Inline field errors shown on blur and submit
- Disable submit button while submitting
- Optimistic updates where appropriate
- Dirty-form warning on navigation

---

## Navigation

- Breadcrumbs on all nested pages
- Active sidebar item highlighted
- Back buttons on detail/edit pages
- Preserve filters/pagination in URL search params

